assets.name: Shown Down #3/3
assets.description:
I started by burning and spray painting my own CDs. Each one hand painted on the back porch. We would go out at night and distribute them at a show or party, wherever we went. Then do it over again the next day. 

That moved to digital distribution pretty quickly and the art form I was perfecting became no longer relevant. A long journey from that point to the present, along my path I found music for film, Sound Design 
 for CG art and multimedia experiences. Which all got wrapped up into NFTs about a year ago. 

Minting through my own contract brings back a sense of adventure and creative inspiration that I was chasing for years. With this contract as a tool and source to share my art and music I feel empowered again. Connection is empowering, community is at the center of this for me. Having the opportunity to create what we see in our dreams and make a living to continue is a dream come true. 

Almost every day and night I dreamt of having a studio where I can create and express my ideas and invite my friends to play in this world with me, this was a goal and dream. Now I sit in my studio and continue to create and bring my family, friends, artists and community into the world I’ve created. Not only artists and creators can access this world, collectors are also now an integral aspect to the process. I’ve always known and appreciated the support I’ve gotten for my music and art, now there is a direct connection between the two. 

This connection is my focus. Access to the deep work I create, work that lives close to my heart, this is all one step closer and easier for me to share and invite people to be a part of the experience, being a part of the source, holding assets like I hold assets, the treasure keepers.
